Steps to create virtual environment
method 1: vs code command palette
1. open ur project in VS code
2. Press Ctrl+shift+P
3. Type "Python: Create Environment"
4. Select "Venv"
5. Select your Python installation
6. VS Code creates and activates everything for you


when working on different projects at the same time and these projects need different version then we use this virtual environment which allows us to use different versions

method 2: Terminal Command
1. open terminal in VS code (view>terminal)
2. Make sure u r in ur project folder
3. Run this command: python -m venv .venv
